---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Caption Outbound" description="Book meetings with decision-makers using our AI Visibility lead-in. We don't just call; we report technical gaps.">
	<main class="container animate-fade-in">
		<header class="service-header" style="padding: var(--space-xl) 0;">
			<p class="section-meta">DISTRIBUTION_SERVICE // CAPTION_OUTBOUND</p>
			<h1 class="text-gradient">Caption Outbound</h1>
			<p class="hero-subtitle">Convert authority into contracts via hyper-targeted outbound systems.</p>
		</header>

		<section class="blueprint-grid">
			<div class="phase surface">
				<div class="phase-number">01 // TARGETING</div>
				<h3>The Precision Layer</h3>
				<p>We use <a href="/protocol/the-llm-indexing-gap">AI Audit data</a> to identify prospects currently invisible to agents. This gives our outreach a "Fiduciary Responsibility" hook rather than a generic pitch.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="phase surface">
				<div class="phase-number">02 // OUTREACH</div>
				<h3>The Authority Lead-In</h3>
				<p>Our SDRs use the proprietary <strong>AI Gap Script</strong>. We report a technical failure in their brand visibility, positioning us as specialists helping them fix a critical problem.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="phase surface">
				<div class="phase-number">03 // RESULTS</div>
				<h3>Infrastructure Handover</h3>
				<p>We book high-intent meetings directly into your calendar. Every lead is pre-qualified and pre-sold on the need for the <a href="/services/authority-loop">Authority Loop</a> protocol.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section" style="background: var(--color-surface); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
			<h2 class="text-gradient">The SDR Evolution</h2>
			<p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.8;">Decision-makers in 2026 are immune to generic "I can help you grow" pitches. They are, however, terrified of being invisible to the procurement bots and AI agents their customers use. When we show them the gap, they listen.</p>
			<div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
				<a href="/roadmap" class="btn btn-outline">View Distribution Roadmap</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section container text-center">
			<div class="section-meta">READY_TO_SCALE</div>
			<h2 class="text-gradient">Scale your distribution.</h2>
			<p style="margin: 1rem auto; max-width: 600px; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Combine cold outreach with our <a href="/services/authority-loop">Authority Loop</a> to create an unstoppable market position.</p>
			<a href="/audit" class="btn btn-primary" data-astro-prefetch>Run Product Readiness Audit</a>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.service-header { text-align: center; }
	.hero-subtitle { font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
	
	.blueprint-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: var(--space-md);
		margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
	}

	.phase {
		padding: var(--space-lg);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: 12px;
		background: var(--color-surface);
	}

	.phase-number {
		font-family: monospace;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: var(--color-accent);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
	}

	.phase h3 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
	.phase p { color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; }

	@media (max-width: 992px) {
		.blueprint-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
	}
    
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .service-header { padding: var(--space-lg) 0 !important; }
        .hero-subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    }
</style>
